Reasoning: The problem of planning a collision-free path for a robot is a classic problem in robotics, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of a cost function to balance path length and risk-exposure time suggests that this problem may also fall under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The problem may also involve computer vision techniques for detecting and avoiding risk zones, which falls under the category of Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of a penalty function for accumulative time spent in risk zones suggests that this problem may also fall under the category of Control Systems (cs.SY).
